<h2 id=3D"mutable">Mutable</h2>

<p>ASTs are usually mutable, this is great for tools like transpilers, but =
it is not fit for linters, which are for the most part static. This ties ba=
ck to <a href=3D"https://rdambrosio016.github.io/rust/2020/09/18/pure-ast-b=
ased-linting-sucks.html##Expensive-to-clone">Expensive to clone</a>, you ca=
n=E2=80=99t just give out nodes without either cloning or taking a referenc=
e to them.</p>

<p>However, i should add, mutable ASTs are great for autofix, however, auto=
fix is a relatively small part of linting, and it is not worth it to make r=
ule checking a mess so autofix can work great. Additionally, autofix with i=
mmutable trees is not impossible, it is just slightly harder than using mut=
able trees.</p>

<h2 id=3D"next-to-no-error-recovery">Next to no error recovery</h2>

<p>Error recovery refers to a parser being able to take in incorrect source=
 code, and still parse a mostly correct AST out of it. Most linters do not =
attempt this at all, for example, espree, and swc_ecmascript (ESLint and de=
no_lint=E2=80=99s parsers respectively) make no attempt at recovery. When t=
he parsers encounter an error they return an Err result and quit parsing, p=
roducing no AST.</p>

<p>Why is that? well, you can=E2=80=99t just make an AST node field if you =
have no data (duh). If the parser expected an expression which is a field i=
n the AST node, then what are we going to put for the struct?, simple, we d=
ont make the struct and stop parsing :)</p>

<p>This means it is impossible for the linters to lint wrong code, which is=
 an amazing feature for on-the-fly linting in things such as IDEs. Not havi=
ng AST fields to worry about allows rslint to parse this invalid code:</p>

<div class=3D"language-js highlighter-rouge"><div class=3D"highlight"><pre =
class=3D"highlight"><code><span class=3D"k">if</span> <span class=3D"kc">tr=
ue</span> <span class=3D"p">{</span>
  <span class=3D"cm">/* */</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span> <span class=3D"k">else</span> <span class=3D"p">=
{</span>
  <span class=3D"cm">/* */</span>
<span class=3D"p">}</span>
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>And lint it successfully:</p>

<div class=3D"language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class=3D"highlight=
"><pre class=3D"highlight"><code>error[SyntaxError]: Expected token `L_PARE=
N` but instead found `TRUE_KW`
